#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=DS : No , she 's just another co-worker , who I 've never even met .
#Text=We 've just spoken on the phone once .
#Text=She has a kind voice .
#Text=But I have acted this out in my head often , as a way to give myself a chuckle .
#Text=To actually do it would be mortifying .
#Text=It might scare her and I would n't want to do that .
#Text=JM : Maybe you would .
#Text=That 's what Freud would say .
#Text=There 's a dynamic behind that , which is not so easily apparent , but when you think about it or you analyze it , there might be some reason behind it .
#Text=Or Barbara might actually be a stand-in for somebody else that you really would like to have somebody from the living dead come and ...
#Text=DS : [ Laughs ]
#Text=But would that be a pathology , that I 've acted this harassing phone call out in my head ?
#Text=And if it 's not a problem , is it because the act is relatively harmless , as opposed to wanting to drown my baby ?
#Text=JM :
#Text=No. You are enjoying it , you are laughing about it , it 's doing something for you .
#Text=It 's not causing anybody pain or grief .
#Text=It 's not like you are staying up nights worrying about Barbara is going to see your name and you are going to lose your job , and you ca n't eat anymore .
#Text=Based on this scenario ... it 's a joke ! But as Freud would say , jokes are n't just jokes .
#Text=They have a meaning .
#Text=And if you can get beyond that and understand it , you might learn something that 's a little different than what you are saying .
#Text=There might be a meaning .
#Text=DS : Such as , why do I find violating a social norm or more amusing ?
#Text=JM : Yeah .
#Text=It might be particular to Barbara , or who ' Barbara ' represents .
#Text=When you talk about Night of the Living Dead there 's a connection immediately there to this person and this wish .
#Text=DS : Is there always a connection ?
#Text=For instance , just that opening of the movie sticks in my head and I do n't meet many Barbaras .
#Text=It was just something that popped into my head , synapses fired .
#Text=And that movie did play a role in my life , trust me .
#Text=But would it always signify something deeper than that ?
#Text=JM : An orthodox analytic position would be that there is always something deeper than that .
#Text=I think practically , sometimes a cigar is just a cigar .
#Text=Cultural psychology in the United States today
#Text=DS : Have you noticed any affect that the current political culture has had on your patients , in terms of the Iraq War ?
#Text=Either in pathologies where the war is manifesting itself , or in just a general discomfort with the state of the culture and society as it is ?
